body:
@pquentin thanks for your comments :)

I'm afraid I cannot see any value yet in checking the coverage of test files. I think such kind of meta-coverage is a bug, not a feature ;)

Whenever you want a failing test to output some descriptive message you're going to have an 'uncovered path' when such test passes. In the particular case of this PR, there's a test that lets the developer know that he/she forgot to include pricing info for the EC2 regions he/she added. Unless we get rid of such message, the 'coverage' will decrease.
